race.comment: MARTY MCFLY (14) returned from a spell and was in contention on the corner before fading late beaten 3.5L at Wodonga. Had won a Bendigo jumpout and has plenty up the sleeve. This is winnable with the extra fitness. Wary of ENDLESS ELLIEGANCE (3), who debuts for the sharp McEvoy yard. Won as he liked in a recent jumpout and has the blinkers on and a 3kg claim. Draws wide but is likely good enough to manage.   THE NEPHILIM (2) resumes having his first run for a new yard. Placed in a recent jumpout and Kersley rides from a low. He's raced well in better Maidens and has to be considered. NEEDLESTICK (10) debuts and has jumped out well. Yendall stays aboard, and she can feature with average luck in the run. SOMETHING WHITE (7) peaks and is showing enough to suggest she can get some of the purse.
